                      <span>2005-05-06</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>Confused concepts = confusing conclusions. A little bit of everything is a whole bunch of nuthin'. Hodgepodge of unholy hash. By pouring his own unclear internal definitions into crucial Christian words, while being deliberately vague about precise usage (I mean this and not that vs. whatever you feel I mean), readers are misled about just what lexicon he's using. It makes one wonder just what Christ he has in mind? Something that he has come to his own terms with? Or Jesus of Nazareth now at God's Right Hand Who can only be taken on His terms and no others?  </span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">magnanimous paganism for modern spiritual age</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>1</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>37</span>
                      /
                      <span>76</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2005-04-29</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>i was almost in tears reading this. it started out so hopeful. as a Jesus-follower i was expecting to see Jesus worshipped. nowhere could i find brian say he was a Jesus-worshipper.
<br />
<br />he talks a lot about following the way of Jesus and respecting Him and even honoring Mary. but not once could i see brian agree to exclusive worship of Jesus as Deity as equal to glorifying His Father. what did i read instead? it's o.k. to learn and pick up valuable spiritual things from idol-religions who worship allah and other falsegods. it's o.k. to share about following Jesus with pagan idolatrous people, but no need to persuade them to abandon idolatry and turn to the Living God and worship Jesus alone. 
<br />
<br />the Scriptures command the people of the world to worship Him Who sits on the throne AND The Lamb Who frees us from our sins by His Blood. we are warned constantly and compassionately to keep ourselves from idols and false gods. what does brian do? nullify God's express command by substituting his permission to allow people to remain as false god worshippers but still follow Jesus in some way they can be comfortable with.
<br />
<br />wrong, with all due respect. anathema! as Paul says.
<br />
<br />the bible-christian mission is first and foremost a non-negotiable, not-up-for-revision message: we are bringing you pagans good news, telling you to turn away from these worthless things (allah, idols, hindu god/goddess, animism,polytheism) to the Living God Who made heaven and earth and all things.in the past God overlooked such ignorance but now He commands all people everywhere to repent. for He has set a day when He will judge the world with justice by the Man Jesus He has appointed, giving proof of this to all mankind by raising Him bodily from the dead.
<br />
<br />my tears and prayers and broken heart for brian and his followers are that they are leading souls into endorsing or condoning paganism through the door marked christianity.
<br />
<br />if people don't need to turn away from false gods to the True God Jesus Christ to be saved, they won't be saved by staying pagan vishnu or allah or you name it worshippers who are open to the teachings of the Lord but NOT the Lord of the teachings. respecting many(not ALL of them, naturally) of Jesus' teachings like thomas jefferson (deist) or mahatma gandhi (pagan hindu) claimed and selectively following His ways apart from worshipping Jesus as True God is another salvation-by-works religious cult under an assumed identity. it's an impostor-faith.
<br />
<br />if pagans can be saved by worshipping their idol false gods and optionally follow Jesus' teachings and way of life, then so can cults like jehovah witness, mormon, new agers and even agnostics and atheists who admire and respect Jesus' moral ethics as a code to live by but refuse to worship Christ as God. 
<br />
<br />you're either a Jesus-worshipper or not. if not, you're not truly saved by the True God named Jesus. that's what the Scriptures from Genesis to Revelations offer all mankind. "when God brings His Firstborn into the world, God says Let all God's angels worship Him." 
<br />
<br />true or false? JesusGod or idolgods? whoever is not with Me is against Me, Jesus said. Him inviting anyone to follow doesn't mean just embrace His way of living and moral principles or accept Him as a king or a lord or a rabbi or a master. it means WORSHIP JESUS as TRUE GOD or be forever lost in this world and the next.</span>
                  
              
